th log(L_radio,\nobserved/L_radio, SF)=0.6-1.3 depending on quasar type and star formation\nestimator. Although radio-quiet quasars in our sample lie close to the 8-1000\nmicron infrared / radio correlation characteristic of the star-forming\ngalaxies, both their infrared emission and their radio emission are dominated\nby the quasar activity, not by the host galaxy.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 30 Oct 2015 20:00:14 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 24 Nov 2015 22:15:22 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-12-16"}
