his demonstrates that, even over the\nrelatively short WR-phase timescale, tidal and/or other effects causing\nrotational spin-down must be efficient. A challenge to tidal synchronization\ntheory is that the two longest-period binaries in our sample (with periods of\n29.7 and 78.5 days) unexpectedly display super-synchronous rotation.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 30 Oct 2015 23:04:09 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 27 May 2016 15:18:38 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 26 Aug 2016 22:47:41 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-08-30"}
