ng to\nre-inflate a cold planet to its equilibrium configuration. We find that while\nit is possible to re-inflate a cold planet, the re-inflation timescales are\nlonger by a factor of $\\approx 30$ than the cooling time.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 31 Oct 2015 14:50:19 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 6 Mar 2016 16:41:21 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-03-08"}
